1 olive oil
1 sweetcorn
1 beef strips
1 garlic paste
1 cucumber
1 lemon
1 Shredded Cabbage Mix
1 Mini Flour Tortillas
1 sour cream
1 coriander

• Drain corn (1/2 tin for 2P /  1 tin for 4P)
• Heat olive oil in a frying pan over high heat
• Cook beef strips, spice blend, garlic paste and corn, tossing, until browned, 1-2 mins

• Roughly chop cucumber
• Slice lemon into wedges
• In a bowl, combine cabbage, BBQ mayo and a squeeze of lemon juice
• Season and toss

• Microwave tortillas for 10 second bursts, until warmed through
• Fill tortillas with beef mixture, slaw, cucumber and Cheddar
• Top with sour cream and torn coriander
• Serve with remaining lemon wedges